      "help": {
        "overview": "The Missile menu simulates notional ballistic missile launches: anything from a single custom shot between two points on Earth to scripted mass raid scenarios between nuclear powers. Trajectories use a realistic ballistic model, but every launch is fictional. Use it to exercise sensor coverage, missile warning timelines, and what-if scenarios.",
        "imgAlt": "The Create Missile Attack menu with attack type, launch, and target options",
        "imgCaption": "Pick an attack type, then a launch location and target for custom missiles.",
        "typesHeading": "Attack Types",
        "types": "<strong>Custom Missile</strong> launches a single missile you configure. The remaining options, such as <strong>Russia to USA</strong> or <strong>USA to China</strong>, load a scripted mass raid scenario that launches many missiles at once. Land based launch sites use fixed silo coordinates from open source reporting; submarine entries let you type the launch latitude and longitude. Targets are preset cities, or choose <strong>Custom Impact</strong> to enter exact coordinates.",
        "howToUse": "<ol><li>Open the <strong>Missile</strong> menu from the bottom bar (it lives in the Create menu mode).</li><li>Choose a <strong>Type of Attack</strong>. Picking a preset raid launches it immediately when you submit; picking <strong>Custom Missile</strong> reveals the launch and target controls.</li><li>For a custom missile, choose the <strong>Launch Location</strong> and <strong>Target Location</strong>. Submarine entries unlock the custom launch latitude and longitude fields, and <strong>Custom Impact</strong> unlocks the target coordinate fields.</li><li>Click <strong>Launch Missile Attack</strong>. The missile is created and the search bar fills with RV_ so all active missiles are highlighted.</li><li>Use <strong>Show All Missiles</strong> at any time to repeat that search.</li></ol>",
        "tip1": "Launches use the current simulation time, so set the clock first if the scenario should start at a specific moment.",
        "tip2": "Every missile's name starts with RV_, so searching RV_ in the search bar finds all active missiles.",
        "tip3": "If a launch is rejected, a toast explains why; some site and target combinations are outside the missile's modeled range."
      },
      "sections": {
        "attackType": "Attack Type",
        "launch": "Launch",
        "target": "Target"
      }
